caption:
Where do we sign up? ⚽️🙌

After a day of blind football training, Toby challenged a team of sighted footballers to a blind penalty shoot out - who do you think won? VOTE BELOW ⬇️

Thanks to @RNIB and Fulham Football Club for hosting our session 🫶 

Toby Addison’s involvement in the campaign has been facilitated and paid for by LADBible.

[Video Description: Title card reads: ‘BLIND FOOTBALLER SCHOOLS 5-A-SIDE TEAM AT PENALTIES’. Toby opens the video wearing all-black sportswear with the RNIB logo. He holds a white football at an indoor football pitch. Sighted footballers wear white t-shirts with the RNIB logo, black bottoms, and blindfold goggles. While Toby explains Blind Football rules, clips of professional blind footballers scoring a goal are shown. Text reading ‘DRILL 1: DRIBBLING AND SHOOTING’ appears on screen. Toby dribbles and shoots at the goal. He successfully lands the ball in the net. A sighted player wearing blindfold goggles dribbles and shoots. The goalie saves the ball with his foot. Another player attempts to kick the ball and misses, followed by slow motion replay. Another sighted player shoots and scores. He celebrates, running around the pitch with his arms out. The team stand without goggles and ask Toby questions. Text reading ‘DRILL 2: PENALTY SHOOT OUT’ appears on screen. Toby goes first for the penalty shootout to a sighted goalie, followed by the sighted team and so on. The scores go: Toby scores, Team miss (goalie catches), Toby misses the net, Team miss (goalie blocks with foot), Toby scores, Team scores, Toby scores, Team miss the net, Toby hits the bar & ball bounces in as ‘GOAL’ appears on screen, Team scores. Text reading ‘FINAL SCORE: 4-2’ appears on screen, followed by ‘TOBY WINS’. Toby and the team chat on the pitch, goggles off.]
